Dudley Taft and NarragansettCapital Inc said it was prepared to raise its bid to acquireTaft Broadcasting Co to more than 150 dlrs per share.    Taft, through Theta Co, sent and letter to Taft's board ofdirectors stating he was committed to purchasing thebroadcasting company and was ready to discuss all aspects ofthe purchase.    The company said items to be discussed included price,structure and form of consideration. Taft said he was preparedto negotiate a transaction in which Taft Broadcast shareholderswould receive in excess of 150 dlrs per share. Reuter&#3;